Natural Language processing and chatterbots

What does it do? (600 words) 
Natural Language Processing (NLP) bridges the gap between computers and human speech. Some may recall watching episodes of StarTrek where the crew would ask the "computer" to perform an activity or search and the "Computer" would reply. Nowadays we are familiar with this technology in the form of Siri, Alexa or Cortana, where verbal instructions are mainly understood by technology.


